2.10	Zahak	Zahhak	Zahhāk or Zohhāk (in Persian: ‎) is an evil figure in Iranian mythology, evident in ancient Iranian folklore as Aži Dahāka, the name by which he also appears in the texts of the Avesta. In Middle Persian he is called Dahāg or Bēvar-Asp, the latter meaning " 10,000 horses".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Zahhak_enthroned.jpg/150px-Zahhak_enthroned.jpg
